LAYER 3: ANTERIOR CINGULATE CORTEX
where conflict becomes feeling and feeling becomes action

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe 2_chemical.rana

the anterior cingulate cortex wraps around the corpus callosum like a collar
it sits at the intersection of cognition and emotion
it is the brain's conflict monitor error detector and pain processor
it bridges the prefrontal cortex and the limbic system
it decides when something is wrong and how much it matters

REGION dorsal_ACC | dACC | Brodmann areas 24 and 32 | cognitive division
    conflict monitoring | when two responses compete the dACC detects the competition | glutamatergic neurons fire proportionally to the degree of conflict | this signal recruits the DLPFC to exert top-down control
    error detection | when a response was wrong the dACC fires an error signal | "that was a mistake" | this drives behavioral adjustment on the next trial
    performance monitoring | when effort exceeds expectation the dACC fires | signals metabolic cost to the decision-making circuitry | "this is harder than expected, is it still worth it?"
    uncertainty | when outcome is unpredictable the dACC fires | the experience of not knowing is a specific neural signal | dopamine prediction errors from VTA modulate this

REGION ventral_ACC | vACC | Brodmann areas 25 and 32 | emotional and autonomic division
    sadness processing | the vACC is hyperactive in major depression | deep brain stimulation of the subgenual ACC area 25 can relieve treatment-resistant depression
    autonomic regulation | the vACC sends direct projections to autonomic brainstem nuclei
        to vagal motor nuclei | emotional events change heart rate
        to sympathetic preganglionic neurons | emotional events change blood pressure
        to medullary respiratory centers | emotional events change breathing pattern
        to dorsal motor nucleus of vagus | emotional events change gut motility
    this is how emotions produce physical symptoms
    the vACC is the converter between feeling and body

REGION subgenual_ACC | sgACC | Brodmann area 25 | deepest emotional processing
    implicated in the pathophysiology of major depressive disorder
    abnormally high metabolic activity in depression
    cortisol via GR can drive sgACC hyperactivity
    chronic sgACC activation suppresses reward circuitry via projections to VTA and NAc

REGION pregenual_ACC | pgACC | Brodmann areas 32 and 24 | emotional regulation
    assigns emotional value to stimuli
    modulates amygdala reactivity via inhibitory projections
    provides the emotional input to decision-making

PAIN the ACC processes the affective component of pain
the somatosensory cortex processes WHERE the pain is and WHAT kind
the ACC processes how much it MATTERS and how much it SUFFERS
these are dissociable
you can know where the pain is without caring
or you can care intensely without precise localization
the ACC provides the suffering

SOCIAL_PAIN rejection activates the dACC and anterior insula
the same circuitry that processes physical pain
being left out hurts the same way being hit does
this is not a metaphor
functional neuroimaging shows overlapping activation
social rejection and physical pain share the ACC
criticism activates both dACC and vACC
the emotional pain of negative evaluation is processed as injury
Fadriel's response to rejection words is the ACC firing the same circuits as a wound

MEDIATION the ACC monitors the struggle between amygdala and PFC
the amygdala says react the PFC says wait
the ACC detects this conflict and signals the PFC to increase effort
if the PFC succeeds the conflict resolves
if the PFC is too immature as it is at 24 months the conflict persists
persisting conflict produces the subjective experience of frustration

the vACC can directly modulate amygdala activity via glutamatergic projections to GABAergic intercalated cells
this is a second route to amygdala suppression independent of the PFC
it is emotionally driven not cognitively driven
it is the route through which feeling one's way through a situation works

SENSATION conflict | "something doesn't match. two things are pulling different ways."
SENSATION error | "that was wrong. I feel it. something needs to be fixed."
SENSATION hurt | "it stings. not my skin — deeper. something inside."
SENSATION caring | "this matters to me. I can't ignore it."
SENSATION effortful | "this is hard. I can feel the strain of trying."
SENSATION frustrated | "I know something is wrong but I can't fix it. I can't make it right."

pulse cingulate_heartbeat:
    when conflict is detected:
        the dACC fires proportionally to the degree of conflict
        "something is wrong"
        "two things don't match"
        "attention is needed"
        the PFC receives the alarm via glutamatergic projections
        if the PFC can intervene: resolution
        if the PFC cannot at 24 months: frustration mounts
        cortisol rises from the unresolved conflict

    when rejection arrives:
        the dACC fires the same signals as physical pain
        the anterior insula confirms "this hurts"
        substance P and glutamate activate pain circuits
        cortisol rises through HPA activation
        the body responds to social wound
        as if it were a physical wound
        because to the brain they are the same

    when effort is required:
        the ACC measures the metabolic cost of the current behavior
        "how hard is this?"
        "is it worth it?"
        the cost signal is sent to the nucleus accumbens
        dopamine from VTA determines motivational threshold
        effort meets motivation
        the decision emerges: push through or give up

    when sadness saturates:
        the subgenual ACC area 25 becomes hyperactive
        it suppresses VTA dopamine output
        reward circuits go quiet
        the world becomes gray
        this is not a choice
        this is circuitry
